article.headline: SE Louisiana 66, Lipscomb 61
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Tavaris Nance scored 18 points to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 66-61 win over Lipscomb Monday night. Southeastern (7-3) rallied in the second half, hitting 50 percent of its shots, to overcome poor shooting in the first half. Nance hit was 5 of 7 from the field and had three assists. Warrell Span added 12 points and Kevin Green 11 points for the Lions. Lipscomb led 29-24 at the halftime. Brandon Brown led Lipscomb with 18 points, hitting 5 of 7 shots. He also grabbed 12 rebounds. SLU scored 21 points off turnovers to Lipscomb's 15. For the game, SLU hit 21 of its 57 shots and Lipscomb made 23 of its 51 shots.
